1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact sections 49-02-26, 49-02-29, and 49-02-31 of the North
2 Dakota Century Code, relating to renewable electricity and recycled energy credits; and to
3 repeal section 49-02-30 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to energy from hydroelectric
4 facilities.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
6 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 49-02-26 of the North Dakota Century Code is
7 amended and reenacted as follows:
8 49-02-26. Qualifying for renewable electricity and recycled energy credits - Exception
9 for certain hydroelectric facilities.
10 Except as otherwise provided in this section, forFor purposes of qualifying for renewable
11 electricity and recycled energy credits, electricity must be generated from a source identified in
12 section 49-02-25. For electricity generated from hydroelectric facilities, the hydroelectric facility
13 must have an inservice date of January 1, 2007, or later, or be new hydroelectric generation
14 obtained from repowering or efficiency improvements to hydroelectric facilities existing on
15 August 1, 2007.
16 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 49-02-29 of the North Dakota Century Code is
17 amended and reenacted as follows:
18 49-02-29. Qualifying for renewable electricity and recycled energy objective.
19 For purposes of qualifying for the renewable electricity and recycled energy objective
20 contained in section 49-02-28, electricity, except for electricity generated from a hydroelectric
21 facility with an inservice date before January 1, 2007, and electricity that is not obtained from
22 repowering or efficiency improvements to a hydropower facility existing on August 1, 2007,
23 regardless of the source's inservice date, qualifies for meeting the statewide objective provided
